I've had the same problem. Even though I turned Nod32 off in the processes it still kept blocking me.
So I've found a solution without the need to turn Nod32 off! :)

1. Open Nod32
2. Set it to advanced mode (if you haven't done that already)
3. On the top-right corner click "Setup" and then "Advanced setup"
4. Find the tab that says Web access protection and un-check "Enable web access protection".

This will allow you to access any Nod32 blocked site. Just remember to put it back on once you're done.

Hope it helped! :)
